{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review (T3 Integration feasibility overlay) — coaching findings + affirmations. The plan integrates pydantic-ai 1.107.0 anthropic prompt-caching capability, so T3 applies.\n\nAFFIRMATIONS (criteria passed):\n- T3(a) technical_feasibility: the integration is achievable as described. The exact mechanism (AnthropicModelSettings(anthropic_cache_instructions=True, anthropic_cache_tool_definitions=True), anthropic-gated via resolved.startswith(\"anthropic\"), applied at the shared runner seam with no RunRequest content-list change) is sound and matches a working implementation pattern (src/rebar/llm/runner.py:209-222, 421-435).\n- T3(d) critical capability gap routes to SPIKE: the plan correctly front-loads a SPIKE (\"SPIKE FIRST: confirm what pydantic-ai 1.107.0 anthropic_cache_instructions caches for rebar's call shape\") to resolve the load-bearing unknown (does cache_control land on system_prompt= vs instructions=) before committing the implementation — exactly the right routing for a genuine capability uncertainty.\n- T3(b) named API surface (settings keys): anthropic_cache_instructions / anthropic_cache_tool_definitions exist on AnthropicModelSettings — MATCH (verified at src/rebar/llm/runner.py:430-435; docs/experiments/workflow-remediation-pocs/runtime_pydanticai_poc.py:107 uses AnthropicModelSettings).\n\nFINDING (T3(b), MISMATCH on a named library field the plan depends on):\n- [ ] Correct the asserted RunUsage cache-token field names: AC \"On a repeat anthropic container call ... usage.cache_read_input_tokens > 0\" and the \"What\" bullet (\"pin the pydantic-ai 1.107.0 RunUsage field names\") name cache_read_input_tokens. pydantic-ai 1.107.0 NORMALIZES Anthropic's raw cache_*_input_tokens to cache_read_tokens / cache_write_tokens on RunUsage — so the field the AC reads must be usage.cache_read_tokens (the *_input_tokens form is the raw Anthropic API field, not the RunUsage attr). Evidence: tests/unit/test_pydantic_ai_runner.py:322-324 (\"pydantic-ai 1.107.0 normalizes Anthropic's raw cache_*_input_tokens to cache_read_tokens / cache_write_tokens on RunUsage\"); src/rebar/llm/runner.py:416-417 reads getattr(u, \"cache_read_tokens\"/\"cache_write_tokens\"). criteria: [T3]. location: Acceptance Criteria line \"usage.cache_read_input_tokens > 0\" + What bullet \"pin the pydantic-ai 1.107.0 RunUsage field names\". suggested_fix: change the AC assertion to `usage.cache_read_tokens > 0` and note the spike must pin the NORMALIZED RunUsage attr names (cache_read_tokens / cache_write_tokens), distinguishing them from Anthropic's raw cache_*_input_tokens.\n\nNote (not a finding — auth/HTTPS, T3(c)): provider auth/transport is handled by the existing pydantic-ai provider seam already in use; no new auth/HTTPS precondition is introduced by adding model_settings flags, so T3(c) is not-applicable here."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782577512837617001,"uuid":"c8eeb9bc-4c11-4c26-8a79-53d81f956df4"}